9 Relating to Etowah County; to repeal Sections
10 45-28-120, 45-28-140, 45-28-160, and 45-28-220, Code of
11 Alabama 1975, as obsolete.
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
13 Section 1. (a) Section 45-28-120, Code of Alabama 1975,
14 requiring Etowah County to pay health insurance premiums of
15 laid-off employees, is repealed.
16 (b) Section 45-28-140, Code of Alabama 1975,
17 authorizing the county commission, by resolution, to allow
18 certain charitable and volunteer organizations to have
19 equipment repaired and to purchase gasoline or motor fuel from
20 the county at cost, is repealed.
21 (c) Section 45-28-160, Code of Alabama 1975,
22 authorizing any county officer or person designated to draw
23 warrants or checks on the county treasury to use mechanical or
24 facsimile devices for signatures on warrants or checks, is
25 repealed.
26 (d) Section 45-28-220, Code of Alabama 1975, requiring
27 every applicant for a license to hold a public concert or
28 other event to have written prior approval from the Etowah
Page 1

other event to have written prior approval from the Etowah
